79.body: How to Monitor the SRE Golden Signals From the Google SRE book: Latency Traffic Errors Saturation USE Method (from Brendan Gregg): Utilization Saturation Errors RED Method (from Tom Wilkie): Rate Errors Duration 5 Signals Rate â€” Request rate, in requests/sec Errors â€” Error rate, in errors/sec Latency â€” Response time, including queue/wait time, in milliseconds. Saturation â€” How overloaded something is, which is related to utilization but more directly measured by things like queue depth (or sometimes concurrency). As a queue measurement, this becomes non-zero when you are saturated, often not much before. Usually a counter. Utilization â€” How busy the resource or system is. Usually expressed 0â€“100% and most useful for predictions (as Saturation is probably more useful).
